WEBVTT

00:00:05.671 --> 00:00:07.271
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

00:00:07.341 --> 00:00:09.041
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

00:00:10.471 --> 00:00:12.941
- No way! Miss!
- I can do this.

00:00:13.581 --> 00:00:16.881
- Fail! Dear Lord!
- I can do it.

00:00:16.981 --> 00:00:18.651
- Let's do this. Let's go!
- Dear Lord.

00:00:19.651 --> 00:00:20.681
Here I go!

00:00:26.621 --> 00:00:27.661
What the...

00:00:30.061 --> 00:00:32.531
Hey, are you kidding me?
What is this?

00:00:32.801 --> 00:00:33.901
Hey, do-over.

00:00:35.331 --> 00:00:37.801
I lost. I'm off.

00:00:38.471 --> 00:00:40.641
- What?
- I'll leave.

00:00:41.471 --> 00:00:42.471
We're moving.

00:00:49.681 --> 00:00:51.781
So it's decided?
We're the ones moving?

00:00:52.251 --> 00:00:53.421
By a coin toss?

00:00:53.851 --> 00:00:54.851
Yes.

00:00:55.151 --> 00:00:57.221
- I lost.
- What?

00:00:57.621 --> 00:00:58.691
How did you toss it?

00:00:59.021 --> 00:01:00.921
Did you roll it? Or did you flick it
with your wrist like this?

00:01:01.361 --> 00:01:04.891
I flicked my wrist
and tossed it in an arc like this.

00:01:05.291 --> 00:01:07.331
Man, you should've rolled it.

00:01:07.401 --> 00:01:10.031
The odds are better that way.
How many rounds did you play?

00:01:10.171 --> 00:01:12.471
Best of 5? Or best of 3?

00:01:13.341 --> 00:01:15.341
- One shot.
- One shot?

00:01:15.941 --> 00:01:19.111
It should've been best of three!
Let's do it over. Come on.

00:01:19.181 --> 00:01:20.441
Get up. Let's go. Hurry.

00:01:21.041 --> 00:01:24.411
- I lost. I can't just do it again.
- Dae Han, sit down.

00:01:24.751 --> 00:01:27.121
Hey, come outside for a second.
I need to talk to you.

00:01:27.181 --> 00:01:28.181
Come on, out.

00:01:30.151 --> 00:01:32.561
What is with him? Seriously...

00:01:35.591 --> 00:01:36.931
Something's fishy.

00:01:37.891 --> 00:01:39.831
Don't you guys also think
he lost on purpose?

00:01:40.201 --> 00:01:42.801
Yes, I think he did it
for our uncle.

00:01:45.101 --> 00:01:47.771
Your dad put a lot of thought
into this decision,

00:01:48.541 --> 00:01:50.941
so let's just go along with it.

00:01:51.741 --> 00:01:54.681
I bet the family next door
is celebrating.

00:01:55.181 --> 00:01:56.181
Tell me about it.

00:01:56.881 --> 00:01:59.121
It must be a huge weight
off their shoulders.

00:02:04.221 --> 00:02:05.991
So you won?

00:02:06.421 --> 00:02:08.161
Yes, I won.

00:02:08.661 --> 00:02:11.361
Honestly, it feels like
a huge weight's been lifted.

00:02:11.791 --> 00:02:14.361
You decided such an important matter
with a coin toss?

00:02:14.931 --> 00:02:17.531
Wait a minute.
What is all this about?

00:02:17.831 --> 00:02:19.941
Woo Jae's family is moving? Why?

00:02:20.271 --> 00:02:22.041
Eun Bin,
weren't you at the family meeting?

00:02:22.341 --> 00:02:24.841
You skipped the family meeting
for that idol's birthday, right?

00:02:25.011 --> 00:02:27.581
We told you, but you were busy
and said to decide on our own.

00:02:27.881 --> 00:02:31.381
This is insane. Grandfather,
we have to do it over. Right?

00:02:31.451 --> 00:02:33.981
- This whole thing is void!
- Quiet!

00:02:34.821 --> 00:02:36.021
Let's go inside, Father.

00:02:36.751 --> 00:02:37.751
No!

00:02:44.331 --> 00:02:46.931
Why does Woo Jae's family
have to move?

00:02:48.161 --> 00:02:51.331
It's uncomfortable having to
run into them all the time.

00:02:51.401 --> 00:02:54.301
Like that's anything new?
It's always been awkward.

00:02:54.401 --> 00:02:56.511
We've endured it for 30 years...

00:02:56.511 --> 00:02:58.271
since our grandma
and their grandad's affair.

00:02:58.341 --> 00:03:00.511
So why do they suddenly
have to move now?

00:03:01.641 --> 00:03:02.881
It was the adults' decision.

00:03:02.951 --> 00:03:05.621
Don't lie.
This was your scheme, wasn't it?

00:03:05.881 --> 00:03:08.051
Me? The coin toss?

00:03:08.421 --> 00:03:10.251
How could I have possibly rigged it
so they would lose?

00:03:10.721 --> 00:03:13.761
I don't care.
I am not letting them move.

00:03:13.821 --> 00:03:15.121
No, I can't let them!

00:03:16.791 --> 00:03:18.331
That little brat. Darn it.

00:03:18.931 --> 00:03:20.731
Her yelling will make my ears bleed.
Goodness.

00:03:29.211 --> 00:03:30.211
Hey.

00:03:31.311 --> 00:03:32.311
Let's do it over.

00:03:32.941 --> 00:03:35.851
- Do what over?
- I'll give you a pass. Toss again.

00:03:35.981 --> 00:03:37.381
Forget it.

00:03:37.581 --> 00:03:39.821
If you were going to chicken out,
why suggest it in the first place?

00:03:40.181 --> 00:03:43.321
Do you know how much I practiced
for the match of the century?

00:03:43.891 --> 00:03:45.351
Why make me jump through hoops
for nothing?

00:03:46.421 --> 00:03:47.421
It was fun, wasn't it?

00:03:47.721 --> 00:03:48.721
Are you serious?

00:03:49.731 --> 00:03:52.061
- Are you really going to move?
- Yes.

00:03:52.631 --> 00:03:56.401
But keep our move a secret for now,
okay?

00:03:56.871 --> 00:03:59.241
Our patients might worry
if word gets out.

00:03:59.241 --> 00:04:00.241
Hey!

00:04:00.301 --> 00:04:03.971
You always said
I took everything from you.

00:04:04.611 --> 00:04:07.041
I'm finally getting out of your way
here in Onjeong.

00:04:07.311 --> 00:04:09.251
So now,
you can do things your way...

00:04:09.511 --> 00:04:12.851
without me
getting on your nerves. Got it?

00:04:28.931 --> 00:04:32.371
Darling,
you've been through so much.

00:04:32.601 --> 00:04:35.771
This hand saved our family,
didn't it?

00:04:36.741 --> 00:04:38.511
He just had to be the bigger man
and act all cool.

00:04:38.881 --> 00:04:40.681
What? What do you mean by that?

00:04:41.611 --> 00:04:42.911
He let me win.

00:04:44.251 --> 00:04:45.251
Really?

00:04:47.551 --> 00:04:48.581
Goodness.

00:04:50.451 --> 00:04:54.121
- You lost on purpose, didn't you?
- I keep telling you, I didn't.

00:04:54.261 --> 00:04:58.061
Liar.
You've never once lost to Bucket.

00:04:58.161 --> 00:04:59.801
Come on, tell me.
You let him win, didn't you?

00:05:00.261 --> 00:05:01.261
You let him win, didn't you?

00:05:01.531 --> 00:05:03.501
Fine, I let him win. So what?

00:05:03.571 --> 00:05:06.741
Why? I told you I don't care!
I'm fine!

00:05:06.801 --> 00:05:10.411
- Enough. Skip breakfast tomorrow.
- Skip breakfast? Why?

00:05:10.471 --> 00:05:13.981
- You have an endoscopy before work.
- No way. Forget it.

00:05:14.341 --> 00:05:16.881
Dae Han, just this once,

00:05:16.981 --> 00:05:18.711
let me do this one thing for you,
okay?

00:05:19.321 --> 00:05:22.751
You've always been sacrificing
and giving things up for me.

00:05:22.821 --> 00:05:25.821
That's ridiculous.
I've never done that.

00:05:25.961 --> 00:05:28.761
You punk.
While Seong Mi and I were residents,

00:05:28.761 --> 00:05:30.491
you were busy
taking care of our kids...

00:05:30.561 --> 00:05:34.261
- and missed out on dating.
- That's not what happened. Hey.

00:05:34.331 --> 00:05:36.831
I didn't marry her
out of desperation.

00:05:36.831 --> 00:05:37.971
I really liked her.

00:05:38.031 --> 00:05:40.541
It was my choice,
but it was the wrong one.

00:05:40.541 --> 00:05:42.871
I'm the one who married a bad person
and had my marriage fall apart.

00:05:42.941 --> 00:05:44.441
Why are you blaming yourself? Why?

00:05:44.511 --> 00:05:47.911
- Stop arguing. My decision's final.
- Whatever!

00:05:48.211 --> 00:05:50.211
Then what are you going to do
about the clinic?

00:05:50.211 --> 00:05:52.521
What about all those patients
who are counting on you?

00:05:52.681 --> 00:05:54.521
What, you think
I didn't think about that?

00:05:54.851 --> 00:05:55.851
I'll handle it.

00:05:56.191 --> 00:05:58.791
No, you're not moving.
Get that through your head.

00:05:59.391 --> 00:06:02.121
Hey, Dae Han! Wait, seriously...

00:06:03.061 --> 00:06:04.291
That stubborn kid.

00:06:09.971 --> 00:06:11.031
Hey.

00:06:12.101 --> 00:06:14.071
I'm thinking of taking a break
and getting a part-time job.

00:06:14.401 --> 00:06:18.141
Don't even say that.
If you quit too, it'll kill Mom.

00:06:18.311 --> 00:06:20.611
I'm not quitting.
I'm just taking a little break.

00:06:20.681 --> 00:06:22.581
Why? Is something going on?

00:06:23.711 --> 00:06:24.881
No, it's nothing.

00:06:26.051 --> 00:06:28.851
I just feel like I'm the only one
not helping out financially.

00:06:35.191 --> 00:06:36.731
Hey, Eun Bin. What's up?

00:06:37.061 --> 00:06:39.801
Woo Jae! Don't move away.

00:06:39.861 --> 00:06:42.301
I'll die before I let you go!

00:06:42.631 --> 00:06:45.271
Hey, Eun Bin. First, just calm down.

00:06:45.331 --> 00:06:48.671
I'll call you back later, okay?
All right, bye.

00:06:49.511 --> 00:06:52.141
What was that?
I think she's actually into you.

00:06:52.941 --> 00:06:55.951
Looks like it.
Gosh, what am I going to do?

00:06:56.051 --> 00:06:59.381
What's there to do?
If you don't like her, just say so.

00:06:59.451 --> 00:07:02.421
I did. But it's useless
no matter how many times I tell her.

00:07:02.421 --> 00:07:05.021
Then just put up with it.
We're moving soon anyway.

00:07:05.451 --> 00:07:08.491
Out of sight, out of mind, right?

00:07:09.391 --> 00:07:11.761
What about you?
How are you and Hyun Bin doing?

00:07:12.961 --> 00:07:16.571
What do you mean?
There's nothing between us.

00:07:20.741 --> 00:07:24.171
Congratulations.
I'm glad the Chairman is better.

00:07:28.311 --> 00:07:31.511
- My dad complimented me today.
- A compliment?

00:07:31.751 --> 00:07:33.781
He was thrilled
when I told him we might get into...

00:07:33.781 --> 00:07:35.451
Hyegyeong Department Store.

00:07:36.021 --> 00:07:37.121
Way to go.

00:07:37.491 --> 00:07:40.521
Honestly, what would you have done
without Pacu Nacho?

00:07:40.591 --> 00:07:41.591
Tell me about it.

00:07:43.031 --> 00:07:44.891
Are you really going back
after just one year?

00:07:45.691 --> 00:07:48.101
Yes. I guess I have to.

00:07:49.331 --> 00:07:52.701
Why did you confess to Gong Ju Ah
if you're only staying for a year?

00:07:53.571 --> 00:07:54.701
Well...

00:07:55.941 --> 00:07:59.941
When I confessed,
I was prepared to stay for good.

00:08:00.011 --> 00:08:01.081
For real?

00:08:01.141 --> 00:08:04.151
Of course. You think I asked her
to just date me for a year?

00:08:04.211 --> 00:08:07.681
Yes. I figured that's why
you got slapped and rejected.

00:08:08.681 --> 00:08:10.651
You've had that "just slapped" look
on your face lately.

00:08:11.251 --> 00:08:13.021
- Have I, really?
- Yes.

00:08:13.991 --> 00:08:16.161
But now, you've got me thinking.

00:08:16.591 --> 00:08:18.631
So if things work out
with Gong Ju Ah,

00:08:18.631 --> 00:08:20.631
you'll settle down in Korea?

00:08:23.301 --> 00:08:24.731
That's all in the past.

00:08:26.241 --> 00:08:31.041
Oh, I think we'll have to use plan B
for the premium line model.

00:08:31.241 --> 00:08:32.371
You mean Dr. Han Seong Mi?

00:08:33.041 --> 00:08:35.241
I thought you'd make her an offer
next week. What happened?

00:08:35.911 --> 00:08:38.951
I heard she's not really interested
in doing commercials or modeling.

00:08:39.721 --> 00:08:40.721
I just think...

00:08:41.681 --> 00:08:43.221
it's going to be too hard
to convince her.

00:08:43.621 --> 00:08:44.651
Really?

00:08:45.791 --> 00:08:47.061
I guess it can't be helped, then.

00:08:48.721 --> 00:08:49.791
One moment.

00:08:59.341 --> 00:09:01.601
Good. It's healed up nicely.

00:09:02.271 --> 00:09:04.671
That's a relief.
It won't leave a scar.

00:09:05.011 --> 00:09:06.011
It's fine.

00:09:07.581 --> 00:09:10.711
Are you really okay with us moving?

00:09:11.511 --> 00:09:13.621
Yes, but...

00:09:14.181 --> 00:09:16.391
can we really afford
to move right now?

00:09:16.891 --> 00:09:18.251
Just trust me.

00:09:18.851 --> 00:09:21.061
You're married to Han Seong Mi,
remember?

00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:26.701
You're right. You're so reliable.
I hit the jackpot marrying you.

00:09:28.161 --> 00:09:29.871
Funny, coming from the guy
who wanted a divorce.

00:09:30.101 --> 00:09:32.971
You need to sleep for that to heal.
Okay, sleep. Go on.

00:09:32.971 --> 00:09:35.041
- Honey.
- Yes?

00:09:36.471 --> 00:09:37.471
Thank you.

00:09:39.071 --> 00:09:43.111
Do you know today is the first time
you've ever put our family first?

00:09:43.481 --> 00:09:44.511
Really?

00:09:45.581 --> 00:09:47.351
In that case, tonight...

00:09:48.451 --> 00:09:52.021
Do you think I could just
sleep here quietly next to you?

00:09:54.221 --> 00:09:56.831
Come on, Seong Mi. Please?

00:09:58.631 --> 00:09:59.801
Turn off the light and come to bed.

00:10:00.461 --> 00:10:02.571
Okay, I'll be really quiet.
I promise.

00:10:04.901 --> 00:10:09.311
First, I'll list the house,
and then the clinic and pharmacy.

00:10:09.571 --> 00:10:10.571
- Then...
- Come on.

00:10:11.541 --> 00:10:12.711
- Why...
- Good grief.

00:10:12.711 --> 00:10:14.211
Why would you put the house
up for sale?

00:10:14.281 --> 00:10:17.481
Goodness, why all this fuss so late?
Give it back and go to bed!

00:10:17.481 --> 00:10:21.921
No, Mom. Just stop. Besides,
this house is too old to sell.

00:10:22.051 --> 00:10:25.721
It doesn't look old at all.
I've put so much love in this house.

00:10:25.821 --> 00:10:26.821
Right, that's my point.

00:10:26.891 --> 00:10:29.061
So how can you sell a house
you've cherished so much?

00:10:30.391 --> 00:10:32.961
I've already made up my mind.
Just do as your brother says.

00:10:33.661 --> 00:10:37.301
Come on, Mom. Why is it always
about what my brother says?

00:10:37.431 --> 00:10:39.601
Why does he get to make decisions
that are supposedly for my own good?

00:10:39.671 --> 00:10:42.711
- Mom, this is blatant favoritism!
- Gosh, be quiet!

00:10:43.971 --> 00:10:47.681
You said you feel sick
whenever you see Dong Suk, right?

00:10:48.441 --> 00:10:52.051
It's not a stomachache.
It's a heartache.

00:10:53.151 --> 00:10:55.991
No, it's really a stomachache.
I'm getting an endoscopy tomorrow.

00:10:56.451 --> 00:10:59.321
Imagine how hard it must be
for Dong Suk to see you, too.

00:10:59.691 --> 00:11:02.291
Well, whatever.
That's her problem, not mine.

00:11:14.971 --> 00:11:16.611
I truly hate you.

00:11:17.211 --> 00:11:18.471
I can't even stand to look at you.

00:11:23.011 --> 00:11:24.051
Ji Hu.

00:11:25.111 --> 00:11:26.121
Yes?

00:11:26.851 --> 00:11:29.151
Am I ugly, honey? Hard to look at?

00:11:29.791 --> 00:11:31.421
Am I all old and fat?

00:11:33.361 --> 00:11:36.191
You're prettier
than all my friends' moms.

00:11:36.531 --> 00:11:38.291
Whatever, you're just saying that.

00:11:58.611 --> 00:11:59.821
Eun Bin, did you sleep well?

00:12:00.581 --> 00:12:03.521
Hyun Bin, you have to do something
about our stepmom.

00:12:04.421 --> 00:12:06.461
What is it now,
so early in the morning?

00:12:07.121 --> 00:12:10.461
Stepmom kicked Woo Jae's family
out of Onjeong!

00:12:11.061 --> 00:12:15.401
- What?
- Ju Ah's family's being kicked out.

00:12:16.101 --> 00:12:17.671
Okay, I get it.

00:12:18.031 --> 00:12:21.801
- I have to go to work. Bye for now.
- What? Wait...

00:12:24.541 --> 00:12:27.911
Hyun Bin! He hung up on me again!
Unbelievable!

00:12:30.081 --> 00:12:31.411
Eun Bin, time for breakfast.

00:12:31.511 --> 00:12:33.581
I'm not eating! Close the door!

00:12:33.581 --> 00:12:35.951
I can't stand you!
You're all in this together!

00:12:36.021 --> 00:12:38.151
This house is a nightmare!

00:12:45.561 --> 00:12:47.601
Eun Bin says
she's not having breakfast.

00:12:47.801 --> 00:12:50.871
We know, Aunt Se Ri.
We heard her yelling from over here.

00:12:51.601 --> 00:12:54.741
But she's not doing it
just to get a rise out of you.

00:12:55.201 --> 00:12:56.941
Does she actually have feelings
for Jeong Han's son?

00:12:57.141 --> 00:13:00.811
It's like we're cursed. Why does
everyone want to be involved...

00:13:00.881 --> 00:13:03.411
- with that family so badly?
- Mom.

00:13:03.511 --> 00:13:07.951
I don't ever want to see
that family again, even after I die.

00:13:08.151 --> 00:13:10.351
Of course.
It's absolutely out of the question.

00:13:11.251 --> 00:13:14.291
Actually, Dad called me
yesterday afternoon.

00:13:14.921 --> 00:13:17.331
What? Why? What did he say?

00:13:18.691 --> 00:13:20.961
He said Uncle Dong Ik
beat him up pretty badly.

00:13:25.631 --> 00:13:27.001
Why would you do that?

00:13:27.201 --> 00:13:29.941
So what?
Is he going to sue me for assault?

00:13:30.241 --> 00:13:31.241
He said he's sorry.

00:13:32.371 --> 00:13:35.511
He also said to tell you
he'll send the child support.

00:13:36.511 --> 00:13:37.511
He'd better.

00:13:38.051 --> 00:13:40.321
Or I'll go kill him myself.

00:13:42.891 --> 00:13:45.451
Thanks, everyone.

00:13:46.221 --> 00:13:49.161
Don't put it off.
File the papers now, Dong Suk.

00:13:49.531 --> 00:13:50.561
I will.

00:13:50.861 --> 00:13:53.701
We don't have assets to divide
or anything to negotiate.

00:13:54.161 --> 00:13:56.371
Stop picking at your food.
You'll scare away your good fortune.

00:13:57.271 --> 00:13:59.671
What good fortune do I even have
to scare away?

00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:05.511
Dad, I'm going to take some time off
until they move out.

00:14:19.051 --> 00:14:22.521
By the way,
shouldn't she get some therapy?

00:14:22.891 --> 00:14:25.291
She'll be right as rain
once that family moves out.

00:14:25.391 --> 00:14:27.901
- Our Eun Bin will feel better, too.
- Right.

00:14:28.301 --> 00:14:30.971
Them moving out is the cure-all
for this whole family.

00:14:31.271 --> 00:14:34.771
Most of all, I'm just so glad
your ordeal is finally over.

00:14:35.141 --> 00:14:37.971
I'll never have to unclog a toilet
with my own hands again, right?

00:14:38.041 --> 00:14:42.541
Gosh, I never said anything,
but it upset me more than you know.

00:14:42.741 --> 00:14:44.581
He swooped in
to meet Councilor Hwang...

00:14:44.581 --> 00:14:46.221
and even got your father's vote.

00:14:46.581 --> 00:14:49.521
He certainly did.
Gong Jeong Han is anything but fair.

00:14:50.121 --> 00:14:53.191
But don't you worry.
That's never going to happen again.

00:14:53.491 --> 00:14:56.761
Before that family moves out,
make sure...

00:14:56.831 --> 00:14:58.831
you secure the presidency
of the Merchants' Association.

00:14:59.061 --> 00:15:02.231
But do you think that jerk
will just hand it over to me?

00:15:02.331 --> 00:15:04.971
If he won't hand it over,
take it no matter what.

00:15:09.441 --> 00:15:12.811
All right, take a deep breath in.

00:15:12.881 --> 00:15:15.211
And breathe out.

00:15:15.541 --> 00:15:17.611
All right, good work, everyone.

00:15:17.611 --> 00:15:18.651
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

00:15:18.651 --> 00:15:22.751
Here's to another
healthy and prosperous day.

00:15:22.851 --> 00:15:27.821
- See you all tomorrow!
- Good work. Go get rich.

00:15:29.731 --> 00:15:30.761
Hey, come here for a second.

00:15:31.061 --> 00:15:32.231
What now?

00:15:33.061 --> 00:15:34.361
When you move out,

00:15:34.601 --> 00:15:38.071
- who takes over the association?
- For crying out loud.

00:15:38.971 --> 00:15:42.241
I'll check the association's bylaws
and consult with the other officers.

00:15:42.641 --> 00:15:45.941
Since you're the vice president,
I'll arrange for you to succeed me.

00:15:46.241 --> 00:15:49.681
- Wait, what's the catch?
- What, is it too easy for you?

00:15:50.211 --> 00:15:51.951
Hey, Bucket! Jeong Han.

00:15:54.151 --> 00:15:55.481
Let's do the coin toss again.

00:15:55.651 --> 00:15:58.051
Why would I?
We settled it fair and square.

00:15:58.221 --> 00:15:59.621
Hey, Dr. Gong!
Your brother's not making any sense.

00:15:59.691 --> 00:16:01.591
What do you mean, not making sense?
My brother obviously let you win,

00:16:01.661 --> 00:16:04.191
- you sneaky-looking punk!
- Hey, you little brat.

00:16:04.191 --> 00:16:07.031
You need an endoscopy before
the clinic opens, so come quickly!

00:16:07.061 --> 00:16:08.101
- Come on.
- I said I want a rematch!

00:16:08.161 --> 00:16:11.301
Nurse Oh, put him under, will you?
Seriously, what's gotten into him?

00:16:11.371 --> 00:16:13.871
- Let go! Let me go! Hey, Bucket!
- Hey!

00:16:13.941 --> 00:16:15.971
Are you happy now that...

00:16:15.971 --> 00:16:18.171
- Goodness, come on.
- you've kicked us out? Hey, Bucket!

00:16:18.241 --> 00:16:20.281
- You didn't eat. Why so strong?
- Bucket!

00:16:24.581 --> 00:16:25.581
This space...

00:16:27.121 --> 00:16:29.751
It's been a long time
since I've set foot in here.

00:16:31.221 --> 00:16:34.521
I'm sure you heard
we've decided to move.

00:16:37.691 --> 00:16:39.731
That must have been
a difficult decision.

00:16:40.731 --> 00:16:42.331
The kids insisted on it.

00:16:43.471 --> 00:16:45.001
You must feel...

00:16:46.101 --> 00:16:48.041
so empty.

00:16:50.411 --> 00:16:51.541
Yes, I do.

00:16:52.811 --> 00:16:54.981
We've been neighbors,
across from each other for 40 years.

00:17:03.851 --> 00:17:06.591
No signs of inflammation.
It looks clean.

00:17:07.861 --> 00:17:10.361
The mucosal lining is
a perfect shade of pink.

00:17:10.931 --> 00:17:14.931
Are you saying the stomachaches
are actually from heartache?

00:17:15.301 --> 00:17:18.301
We still need to check
his colon to be sure,

00:17:18.301 --> 00:17:20.041
but I don't see any organic issues.

00:17:20.271 --> 00:17:21.441
I'm...

00:17:22.401 --> 00:17:24.741
quitting my job at this clinic.

00:17:25.571 --> 00:17:30.511
I'm going somewhere else.
Look, Mom, what I mean is...

00:17:30.781 --> 00:17:33.981
- Mom, we can't move. Jeong Han.
- Hey.

00:17:34.251 --> 00:17:37.821
- You can't close the clinic.
- Hey...

00:17:37.891 --> 00:17:40.261
Wait, what's he saying?

00:17:41.861 --> 00:17:44.991
- Jin Ah, can we talk for a second?
- Sure.

00:17:45.561 --> 00:17:46.701
Gong Jeong Han!

00:17:47.061 --> 00:17:50.631
Hey, Gong Jeong Han!
How... how could you...

00:17:50.831 --> 00:17:54.501
Onjeong... How could you abandon
Onjeong? Hey, Gong Jeong Han!

00:17:54.571 --> 00:17:57.241
Hey! Will you keep it down?
Seriously...

00:17:57.241 --> 00:18:01.241
Hey, brother! If you leave,

00:18:01.681 --> 00:18:05.481
what about the patients in Onjeong
who all count on you?

00:18:05.551 --> 00:18:07.651
How can you just move away?

00:18:08.021 --> 00:18:11.891
- Brother...
- Hey, just go back to sleep. Okay?

00:18:12.191 --> 00:18:13.621
- Sleep tight. Sleep.
- Brother...

00:18:13.991 --> 00:18:15.061
- Go on, get some sleep.
- Brother...

00:18:15.291 --> 00:18:16.961
- Yes, sleep.
- Jeong Han.

00:18:17.531 --> 00:18:19.131
You can't move.

00:18:19.961 --> 00:18:22.261
I'll... I...

00:18:22.931 --> 00:18:25.571
I'll move instead, brother.

00:18:33.111 --> 00:18:34.781
Brother, I'll move instead.

00:18:36.511 --> 00:18:39.011
So you've decided
to leave Onjeong after all.

00:18:40.421 --> 00:18:42.951
To be honest,
I always knew this day would come.

00:18:43.791 --> 00:18:46.321
I'm sorry for making the decision
without talking to you.

00:18:46.721 --> 00:18:50.731
No. You don't have to ask me first.
I'll follow you anywhere.

00:18:51.691 --> 00:18:54.731
It might be a lot farther away.
Are you sure you're okay with that?

00:18:55.261 --> 00:18:56.831
Of course. I don't mind at all.

00:18:58.201 --> 00:19:00.571
I'm worried about the patients,
though.

00:19:02.301 --> 00:19:03.311
I know.

00:19:03.841 --> 00:19:06.111
I just hope
a good doctor takes over.

00:19:07.241 --> 00:19:09.141
So, once
you've wrapped things up here,

00:19:09.411 --> 00:19:11.351
are you planning to move
near Dr. Han's clinic?

00:19:13.321 --> 00:19:15.021
That's the idea,

00:19:15.651 --> 00:19:18.051
but it won't be easy, financially.

00:19:18.521 --> 00:19:21.961
Come on,
with Dr. Han being so successful,

00:19:21.961 --> 00:19:23.061
you don't need to worry.

00:19:27.401 --> 00:19:30.201
Your husband
is also trying very hard.

00:19:30.671 --> 00:19:34.301
And his attitude in our sessions
is remarkably different from before.

00:19:34.971 --> 00:19:35.971
Yes.

00:19:36.371 --> 00:19:39.211
He used to shut down
whenever his family came up,

00:19:39.711 --> 00:19:42.781
but now he really tries
to hear me out.

00:19:43.551 --> 00:19:45.181
Thank you so much, Doctor.

00:19:45.881 --> 00:19:50.791
Remember to use your mood journal
before our next session. Okay?

00:19:50.991 --> 00:19:51.991
Okay.

00:19:53.921 --> 00:19:56.221
Doctor. To be honest,

00:19:56.991 --> 00:20:00.801
I was a little disappointed
when I heard you would be on TV.

00:20:01.861 --> 00:20:06.641
- Why? Afraid I would neglect you?
- Yes.

00:20:07.241 --> 00:20:10.071
I thought you'd change
once you became famous,

00:20:10.341 --> 00:20:13.241
but you're just as attentive
as you've always been,

00:20:13.641 --> 00:20:14.881
and I'm so happy about that.

00:20:16.281 --> 00:20:19.381
I'm so glad you feel that way.
It makes it all worthwhile.

00:20:22.581 --> 00:20:23.951
(Closed for Lunch)

00:20:25.621 --> 00:20:29.061
- Are you off to see Director Song?
- Yes. Have a good lunch.

00:20:29.191 --> 00:20:31.461
- I'll be back.
- Are you signing the contract?

00:20:31.831 --> 00:20:36.261
- For your own show!
- Enjoy your meal.

00:20:36.331 --> 00:20:37.771
- Have a good meeting.
- Thanks!

00:20:41.371 --> 00:20:44.971
Listen, Seong Mi. We must postpone
the launch of your solo show.

00:20:46.541 --> 00:20:50.181
- Oh, really?
- Foreign sales were poor last year,

00:20:50.681 --> 00:20:52.351
so the channel's finances
are a little shaky.

00:20:53.181 --> 00:20:56.181
As a result, they've put a hold on
all new program launches, but...

00:20:56.891 --> 00:20:59.291
don't you worry. I swear,
before the year is out,

00:20:59.551 --> 00:21:02.191
I'm going to push through
your solo show.

00:21:02.961 --> 00:21:03.961
Is there any chance...

00:21:04.761 --> 00:21:07.561
you could draw up the contract
in advance?

00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:10.101
Why? Do you need money?

00:21:11.471 --> 00:21:14.201
I'm thinking about moving our house
and my husband's clinic...

00:21:14.271 --> 00:21:16.971
to somewhere closer to my practice.

00:21:18.171 --> 00:21:20.141
Wow, so Gong Jeong Han
finally caved?

00:21:20.581 --> 00:21:22.581
Good. It's about time.

00:21:23.481 --> 00:21:24.711
But now what?

00:21:25.311 --> 00:21:28.751
I already made a big promise,
thinking the deal was guaranteed.

00:21:29.621 --> 00:21:33.761
Hey. What are you worried about?
There's only one Dr. Han Seong Mi.

00:21:35.521 --> 00:21:39.531
Let's film a commercial.
You've turned down many offers.

00:21:40.061 --> 00:21:42.161
What excuse
would I give my patients?

00:21:42.861 --> 00:21:46.701
I only did the show
as part of patient care.

00:21:47.071 --> 00:21:48.071
Seong Mi.

00:21:48.841 --> 00:21:51.841
Back when I first dragged you
onto TV...

00:21:52.311 --> 00:21:56.211
Do you know why I reached out to you
out of all the other psychiatrists?

00:21:57.111 --> 00:21:59.551
I don't know.
Because I was your first love?

00:22:00.981 --> 00:22:03.491
Of course.
I can't say that wasn't part of it.

00:22:04.391 --> 00:22:05.621
So what was the real reason?

00:22:06.251 --> 00:22:09.761
It's easy to find doctors
who are only in it for the fame.

00:22:10.291 --> 00:22:12.931
But you, then and now,

00:22:13.231 --> 00:22:15.031
always worry
about your patients first.

00:22:16.231 --> 00:22:19.001
Jeong Han isn't the only one
who puts patients first.

00:22:20.141 --> 00:22:21.301
You're just like him.

00:22:23.671 --> 00:22:26.841
So, what was
that commercial offer I got?

00:22:29.111 --> 00:22:30.711
A supplement
for menopausal hair loss?

00:22:32.051 --> 00:22:33.051
What?

00:22:34.381 --> 00:22:37.591
Mom, you specialize
in mental health.

00:22:37.751 --> 00:22:39.121
That's about the mind,

00:22:39.121 --> 00:22:41.621
so isn't hair loss
a different field?

00:22:43.121 --> 00:22:45.931
Mom, let's talk about this
when you get home.

00:22:46.731 --> 00:22:47.761
Okay.

00:22:50.231 --> 00:22:51.971
Is Dr. Han doing a commercial?

00:22:52.231 --> 00:22:56.001
Yes. I guess
beggars can't be choosers.

00:22:56.471 --> 00:22:59.441
Our whole family is depending
on my mom right now.

00:22:59.641 --> 00:23:02.541
If her solo show contract's delayed,
we can't afford to move.

00:23:02.941 --> 00:23:05.711
Seriously, she'd be
the perfect model for us.

00:23:05.851 --> 00:23:08.521
Why did the two families have to
get caught up in a crisis right now?

00:23:15.261 --> 00:23:17.661
The feedback from Hyegyeong
was very positive.

00:23:17.961 --> 00:23:21.001
Pacu Nacho says you did a great job
in the meeting, Ju Ah.

00:23:21.331 --> 00:23:23.831
Thank you, but the real credit
goes to Director Yang.

00:23:24.931 --> 00:23:26.431
Nothing's confirmed yet.

00:23:26.871 --> 00:23:29.501
The Hyegyeong Product Review
for the first half of the year...

00:23:36.381 --> 00:23:37.451
Excuse me.

00:23:38.111 --> 00:23:40.951
He was going to say if we pass,
we'll secure a spot in their store.

00:23:45.851 --> 00:23:49.121
What's wrong?
Why are you so pitiful and sickly?

00:23:52.691 --> 00:23:53.701
I'm sorry.

00:23:57.531 --> 00:23:58.831
Oh, boy.

00:23:59.171 --> 00:24:01.171
I guess since he lived abroad
for so long,

00:24:01.471 --> 00:24:03.841
he's having a hard time adjusting
to the change of seasons in Korea.

00:24:04.441 --> 00:24:05.741
He hardly ever gets sick.

00:24:06.341 --> 00:24:07.941
Could it be heartache?

00:24:08.611 --> 00:24:10.351
Doesn't it look that way
to you too, Ju Ah?

00:24:11.881 --> 00:24:15.681
We passed round one, Vice President.
The presentation is scheduled.

00:24:16.481 --> 00:24:18.221
How rude of you to just ignore me.

00:24:18.821 --> 00:24:21.361
Vice President,
regarding the model you mentioned,

00:24:21.461 --> 00:24:23.861
when are we making
the official offer?

00:24:23.931 --> 00:24:26.131
Oh, Dr. Han Seong Mi.

00:24:26.731 --> 00:24:28.961
Pacu Nacho
put a stop to her casting.

00:24:29.731 --> 00:24:30.731
Pardon?

00:24:31.701 --> 00:24:32.801
It's a shame.

00:24:34.141 --> 00:24:36.271
We'll probably end up
going with another model.

00:24:41.241 --> 00:24:43.611
I guess he feels awkward about it,
right?

00:24:44.051 --> 00:24:45.151
Yes, of course.

00:24:45.681 --> 00:24:47.721
My mom wouldn't have taken
this job anyway.

00:24:48.921 --> 00:24:52.491
Come on. Let's explain the situation
to the Director. What do you say?

00:24:52.991 --> 00:24:55.491
It looks like he decided without
knowing your family's in a bind.

00:24:55.921 --> 00:24:58.361
Forget it. There are
other commercials available.

00:25:01.101 --> 00:25:02.931
I'm going to
look into a company loan.

00:25:04.371 --> 00:25:05.571
Excuse me, Mr. Park?

00:25:06.371 --> 00:25:07.371
Yes?

00:25:10.211 --> 00:25:12.111
Can I speak with you for a moment?

00:25:13.681 --> 00:25:14.681
Sure.

00:25:17.051 --> 00:25:19.251
Don't you say a word. Got it?

00:25:20.081 --> 00:25:21.081
Okay.

00:25:26.821 --> 00:25:27.821
Yes.

00:25:43.871 --> 00:25:45.371
What? What is it?

00:25:45.811 --> 00:25:48.381
What's so important that you had to
drag me all the way out here?

00:25:48.781 --> 00:25:50.311
Why haven't you been showing up
at the clinic?

00:25:50.651 --> 00:25:52.281
What? Is it because
you don't want to see me?

00:25:52.611 --> 00:25:54.651
And what business is that of yours?

00:25:55.651 --> 00:25:56.991
Is that why you called me here,
to lecture me?

00:25:57.051 --> 00:25:59.521
No, that's not it. We're not moving.

00:25:59.591 --> 00:26:01.561
- That's what I came to tell you.
- Why not?

00:26:01.561 --> 00:26:02.691
Why should we have to?

00:26:03.661 --> 00:26:05.591
The adults already decided this.

00:26:05.591 --> 00:26:06.691
We're adults, too.

00:26:06.691 --> 00:26:08.901
This is between you and me.
We should sort this out ourselves.

00:26:08.901 --> 00:26:13.331
No use crying over spilled milk.
You should've reined in your wife.

00:26:13.331 --> 00:26:15.301
Hey, what did you just say?
Ouch, my stomach...

00:26:15.371 --> 00:26:18.371
Why did you marry a woman like that
who seduces married men?

00:26:18.371 --> 00:26:20.681
Hey, are you finished?
Ouch, my stomach...

00:26:20.681 --> 00:26:24.281
She ruined my family!
At least have the decency to move!

00:26:24.281 --> 00:26:27.581
Hey, keep your voice down!
What if the neighbors hear you?

00:26:27.951 --> 00:26:29.021
My stomach...

00:26:29.281 --> 00:26:32.351
Seriously, what is with you?
I'm talking here. How rude!

00:26:32.421 --> 00:26:34.161
Why are you squirming around
like a dog that has to poop?

00:26:34.221 --> 00:26:37.161
It only happens when I see you.
The moment we run into each other...

00:26:38.831 --> 00:26:39.831
What are you talking about...

00:26:40.731 --> 00:26:44.931
- Seeing me makes you need to poop?
- Yes. Hey, let's talk later...

00:26:47.071 --> 00:26:48.741
Let's talk about this later.

00:26:50.941 --> 00:26:53.341
What is with him? That's ridiculous.

00:26:55.081 --> 00:26:56.951
That was so insulting!

00:27:01.781 --> 00:27:04.351
It really hurts!
Hey, during the endoscopy...

00:27:04.351 --> 00:27:05.451
Did you poke something wrong?

00:27:05.451 --> 00:27:07.821
Hey, stop being such a baby
and just hold still.

00:27:10.361 --> 00:27:13.031
Hey. You just saw Dong Suk,
didn't you?

00:27:13.361 --> 00:27:14.631
Yes. How did you know?

00:27:15.131 --> 00:27:18.071
It's stress.
Psychosomatic stomach pain.

00:27:18.371 --> 00:27:20.031
You were fine before you saw her,
weren't you?

00:27:20.271 --> 00:27:22.801
What? Gosh, that's ridiculous.

00:27:22.871 --> 00:27:25.011
How can my stomach hurt
just from seeing someone?

00:27:25.741 --> 00:27:29.541
That's what makes stress so scary.
If you ignore it, it gets serious.

00:27:29.881 --> 00:27:33.181
So stop being stubborn
and just agree to the move.

00:27:34.351 --> 00:27:36.451
- This is driving me crazy. Really?
- Good grief.

00:27:36.451 --> 00:27:38.151
Wait, so if I see Dong Suk...

00:27:39.051 --> 00:27:41.521
- It hurts! Hey, just think...
- Stop being so dramatic!

00:27:41.591 --> 00:27:43.421
- Just thinking about her hurts...
- For crying out loud.

00:27:46.591 --> 00:27:47.601
(Pharmacist Recommended)

00:27:48.201 --> 00:27:49.301
What's this?

00:27:50.131 --> 00:27:51.401
It's cough medicine.

00:27:51.771 --> 00:27:54.241
I figured you might be too busy
to go to the doctor.

00:27:54.741 --> 00:27:58.211
If you don't act fast, it'll linger.
Take it with warm water.

00:28:00.211 --> 00:28:02.311
You don't have to do all this
for me.

00:28:05.081 --> 00:28:07.921
I'd do this much
for any of my colleagues.

00:28:08.121 --> 00:28:10.851
No. I'd rather you didn't.

00:28:12.351 --> 00:28:15.661
So, are we not even allowed
to be friends?

00:28:16.721 --> 00:28:20.761
I just can't be friends
with someone I've had feelings for.

00:28:22.701 --> 00:28:23.901
"Had feelings for."

00:28:33.781 --> 00:28:37.211
You're so incredibly old-fashioned.
Did you...

00:28:37.281 --> 00:28:39.581
come from the Victorian era
or something?

00:28:39.951 --> 00:28:42.481
You can't be friends with someone
you used to have feelings for?

00:28:42.551 --> 00:28:45.121
You should've told me that
before you confessed.

00:28:45.191 --> 00:28:49.591
You should've said if I said no,
we couldn't be friends. Then,

00:28:49.821 --> 00:28:51.961
I wouldn't have let you confess,
Director.

00:28:52.761 --> 00:28:56.131
Because if you hadn't confessed,
we could've at least stayed friends.

00:28:58.201 --> 00:29:00.971
It's not like I turned you down
because I don't like you.

00:29:00.971 --> 00:29:03.371
With our families' situation,
I don't have a choice...

00:29:04.771 --> 00:29:08.481
You know this is hard for me too,
but I had to. You know that.

00:29:09.111 --> 00:29:12.411
- Ju Ah.
- How could you hurt me so much?

00:29:15.051 --> 00:29:17.151
It's because
if you're nice to me, I...

00:29:17.821 --> 00:29:20.361
I'm afraid it will be
hard for me to move on.

00:29:21.291 --> 00:29:24.861
If you keep being so nice,
I'm afraid I'll want more.

00:29:25.591 --> 00:29:29.161
And I think that would make things
even harder on you, Ju Ah,

00:29:29.231 --> 00:29:32.271
and I don't want to hurt you.
So I'm trying my best right now...

00:29:32.331 --> 00:29:33.531
I understand.

00:29:38.741 --> 00:29:40.411
I'm sorry if I hurt your feelings.

00:29:41.041 --> 00:29:44.411
It's fine.
I was the one who crossed the line.

00:29:45.411 --> 00:29:46.411
I'm sorry.

00:30:15.381 --> 00:30:19.081
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:30:22.651 --> 00:30:24.691
(Always Kind Pharmacy)

00:30:25.351 --> 00:30:28.691
- I'm going to the Merchants' Hall.
- Okay.

00:30:29.861 --> 00:30:30.861
Wait.

00:30:31.431 --> 00:30:32.591
What are you looking at?

00:30:34.161 --> 00:30:36.231
Are you looking for a new location
for the pharmacy?

00:30:37.031 --> 00:30:39.531
Yes, but...

00:30:40.171 --> 00:30:43.141
it won't be easy finding someone
to take over the pharmacy.

00:30:44.111 --> 00:30:46.871
Tell me about it.
It's the same for the clinic.

00:30:47.481 --> 00:30:49.681
And also...

00:30:50.341 --> 00:30:51.651
When we move,

00:30:52.011 --> 00:30:53.851
I'm not planning on
opening another pharmacy.

00:30:54.351 --> 00:30:55.351
Wait, why not?

00:30:55.751 --> 00:30:59.721
- You want to retire?
- That's part of it, but...

00:31:00.151 --> 00:31:02.091
If we both open new businesses,

00:31:02.361 --> 00:31:04.461
it'll be too much of a burden
on Seong Mi.

00:31:05.631 --> 00:31:08.961
I know exactly how hard
she works for her money.

00:31:10.731 --> 00:31:13.901
Still, Mom, please think
about it a little more.

00:31:15.401 --> 00:31:17.041
I will. Now, go on.
You should get going.

00:31:17.371 --> 00:31:18.371
Okay.

00:31:25.051 --> 00:31:29.151
Here's the member roster,
and this is the dues account book.

00:31:29.321 --> 00:31:31.551
And this is the official seal,
so don't lose it.

00:31:32.421 --> 00:31:37.091
Here are members with overdue fees.
Try to work it out with them kindly.

00:31:37.691 --> 00:31:38.691
Got it.

00:31:39.361 --> 00:31:42.731
This has all the official notices
from the local government.

00:31:43.061 --> 00:31:46.601
Don't miss any deadlines,
and apply for all eligible grants.

00:31:47.031 --> 00:31:48.041
- I got it.
- All right.

00:31:52.071 --> 00:31:54.441
Hey, Seong Tae.
Did you ask that junior doctor?

00:31:56.041 --> 00:31:57.411
Really?

00:31:58.111 --> 00:32:01.551
I thought he wanted his own clinic.
Why, did he say no?

00:32:02.121 --> 00:32:04.921
This is a great opportunity.
Have him come and see it, okay?

00:32:05.591 --> 00:32:09.721
All the equipment is included.
It's a great turnkey operation.

00:32:10.691 --> 00:32:13.961
Man, the people at this market
are so warm and friendly,

00:32:14.031 --> 00:32:15.931
and if he were to practice here...

00:32:17.471 --> 00:32:20.841
Oh, I see. All right.

00:32:21.241 --> 00:32:23.341
Yes, I'd appreciate it
if you'd ask around a little more.

00:32:23.971 --> 00:32:24.971
Okay.

00:32:28.111 --> 00:32:29.341
Hold on.

00:32:29.641 --> 00:32:32.381
Where did I put that
facility safety management manual?

00:32:34.821 --> 00:32:35.921
Hey.

00:32:36.321 --> 00:32:37.751
Why are you leaving
everything behind?

00:32:38.221 --> 00:32:40.151
Aren't you opening a new practice
next to Seong Mi's clinic?

00:32:40.921 --> 00:32:43.561
Easy for you to say.

00:32:43.621 --> 00:32:48.161
Where am I going to get the money?
I barely have enough for the move.

00:32:48.231 --> 00:32:49.861
Oh, here it is. Here you go.

00:32:54.741 --> 00:32:56.501
You're going to be in a commercial,
Seong Mi?

00:32:56.641 --> 00:32:59.011
Mom, is it for that supplement
you mentioned earlier?

00:32:59.611 --> 00:33:03.741
Yes, and Director Song set me up
with other places that contacted me.

00:33:03.881 --> 00:33:06.751
But I thought you said
you'd never do any commercials.

00:33:07.051 --> 00:33:08.481
Are you only doing it
because you have to?

00:33:09.121 --> 00:33:10.621
That's part of it, but...

00:33:11.851 --> 00:33:14.661
Now that it's actually happening,
I'm kind of excited.

00:33:15.521 --> 00:33:17.761
Honey. Near my clinic,

00:33:17.831 --> 00:33:20.091
I found a place that looked good
for you to open your new practice.

00:33:20.831 --> 00:33:22.561
Oh, Seong Mi.

00:33:22.761 --> 00:33:24.871
I'm not going to open
a new practice.

00:33:24.871 --> 00:33:26.001
What?

00:33:26.371 --> 00:33:28.101
You're not? Why not?

00:33:28.601 --> 00:33:32.411
Even after we move, I feel like
this market still needs a clinic.

00:33:33.211 --> 00:33:34.481
So I'll leave everything here,

00:33:35.041 --> 00:33:36.281
and I'm thinking of...

00:33:36.281 --> 00:33:38.811
just looking for a salaried job
at another hospital.

00:33:38.911 --> 00:33:39.911
What do you think, Mom?

00:33:40.181 --> 00:33:41.181
Jeong Han.

00:33:41.251 --> 00:33:44.221
To be honest, Dad,
it's financially less risky.

00:33:44.821 --> 00:33:47.461
But will we find a doctor
to take over our clinic?

00:33:47.721 --> 00:33:49.961
Yes, I'm looking into it.

00:33:51.431 --> 00:33:55.631
I'll try to find a doctor
passionate about community care.

00:33:56.361 --> 00:33:57.371
Okay.

00:33:57.901 --> 00:34:02.141
I'll look for hospitals
near wherever we end up moving.

00:34:02.401 --> 00:34:05.411
So, Dae Han, you should start
looking for a new clinic, too.

00:34:06.071 --> 00:34:10.581
I told the landlord
that we'll be moving out,

00:34:11.081 --> 00:34:14.281
but we still have time on our lease,
so if we can't find a new tenant,

00:34:14.621 --> 00:34:17.791
we'll probably have to
keep paying the rent ourselves.

00:34:17.891 --> 00:34:22.221
Mom. We should just wait.
What's the rush to move out now?

00:34:23.461 --> 00:34:25.861
I already told Jeong Han.

00:34:26.131 --> 00:34:28.631
Once we move, the pharmacy...

00:34:29.261 --> 00:34:30.771
I'm not going to
reopen the pharmacy.

00:34:31.071 --> 00:34:33.571
Mom, if you stop working,
you'll get old fast.

00:34:36.571 --> 00:34:37.911
I'm already old.

00:34:38.611 --> 00:34:40.141
Besides, I deserve a break.

00:34:41.341 --> 00:34:45.981
I've always worked and run the home.
It's been hard on me, too.

00:34:46.811 --> 00:34:48.181
I mean it.

00:34:49.151 --> 00:34:50.321
I agree.

00:34:51.121 --> 00:34:53.291
Mother,
you should get some rest now.

00:34:54.061 --> 00:34:57.361
Stopping work will make you age?
Who came up with that nonsense?

00:34:57.361 --> 00:34:59.861
Tell me about it.
Taking a break is the best.

00:35:02.201 --> 00:35:03.461
Right. Anyway...

00:35:04.331 --> 00:35:06.501
Since we've all decided
on a fresh start,

00:35:06.671 --> 00:35:11.171
let's drop all our baggage
and travel light.

00:35:11.441 --> 00:35:12.711
Both physically and emotionally.

00:35:13.341 --> 00:35:14.341
All right?

00:35:15.441 --> 00:35:16.511
Yes?

00:35:20.311 --> 00:35:24.121
Hey, by the way,
why did the Director call you?

00:35:26.021 --> 00:35:30.021
He needed some files for a meeting.
Why?

00:35:30.691 --> 00:35:34.831
You didn't tell him about my family,
did you?

00:35:35.761 --> 00:35:37.061
You told me not to.

00:35:37.601 --> 00:35:40.431
You scared me, so I didn't.
I should have, though.

00:35:40.671 --> 00:35:43.401
No, I was just wondering if you had.

00:35:44.671 --> 00:35:46.671
- Gong Ju Ah.
- Hey, okay, I have to go. Bye.

00:35:47.011 --> 00:35:48.111
Yes, Mom?

00:35:50.581 --> 00:35:53.211
Didn't you say you had something
to talk to me about after work?

00:35:53.751 --> 00:35:57.221
It's not that
I had something specific to say.

00:35:57.351 --> 00:35:59.791
I just kind of wanted to talk,
you know?

00:36:00.451 --> 00:36:02.891
You silly goose.
If you have nothing to say, I'll go.

00:36:02.891 --> 00:36:04.161
Mom, wait.

00:36:05.031 --> 00:36:09.001
Any good offers for the commercials?
Anything that caught your eye?

00:36:09.601 --> 00:36:11.101
Nothing special.

00:36:11.601 --> 00:36:12.771
Mostly for supplements.

00:36:13.331 --> 00:36:17.141
I'm meeting advertisers next week.
I'll decide after I meet them.

00:36:22.111 --> 00:36:23.741
Hello, this is Han Seong Mi.

00:36:25.811 --> 00:36:26.811
I'm sorry, who's calling?

00:36:29.481 --> 00:36:31.251
I see. Yes.

00:36:32.651 --> 00:36:33.651
Right.

00:36:36.591 --> 00:36:38.691
What's going on?
That sounds like a man.

00:36:39.431 --> 00:36:40.431
Is it one of the advertisers?

00:36:48.771 --> 00:36:50.911
Eun Bin, I'm home.

00:36:51.141 --> 00:36:54.211
You're here? Was stepmom so excited
she threw a party?

00:36:54.381 --> 00:36:58.081
Yes. You're still in your pajamas.
You skipped lunch, didn't you?

00:36:58.451 --> 00:36:59.851
None of your business.

00:37:00.151 --> 00:37:01.351
Are you really not going to eat?

00:37:02.351 --> 00:37:03.351
Get out!

00:37:04.151 --> 00:37:06.351
Nice catch! Here, catch!

00:37:06.721 --> 00:37:07.891
Come on!

00:37:08.421 --> 00:37:09.621
Get out!

00:37:10.321 --> 00:37:11.431
Unbelievable.

00:37:12.161 --> 00:37:14.361
There's no one on my side.
No one at all.

00:37:15.531 --> 00:37:17.361
My goodness, what a spread.

00:37:17.601 --> 00:37:19.531
You didn't seem
to have much appetite,

00:37:19.531 --> 00:37:20.731
and Hyun Bin is here, too.

00:37:21.471 --> 00:37:24.771
- I'm seeing a lot of you lately.
- I have an errand nearby tomorrow.

00:37:25.341 --> 00:37:26.571
Why? You have a problem with that?

00:37:26.941 --> 00:37:27.941
Let's eat.

00:37:29.281 --> 00:37:32.511
Hyun Bin, once your dad takes over
the Merchants' Association,

00:37:32.511 --> 00:37:35.721
he'll get the nomination
and then run for city council.

00:37:37.351 --> 00:37:40.491
Nowadays, branding is crucial
even for politicians.

00:37:40.551 --> 00:37:44.591
How about you, as a branding expert,
give your father some advice?

00:37:45.661 --> 00:37:49.161
Instead of photo-op volunteer work,
do something sincere.

00:37:49.601 --> 00:37:50.701
And you call yourself an expert?

00:37:51.301 --> 00:37:52.601
What did you even learn
studying abroad?

00:37:52.931 --> 00:37:54.401
You're just stating the obvious.

00:37:54.641 --> 00:37:58.211
You're in this mess because
you can't even do the obvious.

00:37:58.371 --> 00:37:59.371
Just you watch, you little punk.

00:37:59.711 --> 00:38:04.411
By the way, Gong Dae Han called me
and said he refuses to move.

00:38:04.681 --> 00:38:06.751
My gosh, what are you talking about?

00:38:07.211 --> 00:38:11.351
He threw a fit about not moving,
then suddenly had to poop and ran.

00:38:11.991 --> 00:38:13.991
Gosh, not while we're eating!

00:38:14.361 --> 00:38:15.621
You know
I have a weak stomach, right?

00:38:16.121 --> 00:38:20.261
Wait, didn't they promise to move?
They're not backing out, are they?

00:38:20.431 --> 00:38:22.161
You haven't heard anything?

00:38:23.461 --> 00:38:25.131
It looks like
they're trying to move,

00:38:25.831 --> 00:38:27.571
but it seems they're having
some financial trouble.

00:38:27.571 --> 00:38:30.701
Gosh, seriously? Dr. Han is on TV
and has published books.

00:38:30.941 --> 00:38:33.471
What does she do with all her money?
Right, Hyun Bin?

00:38:33.911 --> 00:38:37.411
Shooting commercials would pay more,
but she doesn't have her own show.

00:38:37.481 --> 00:38:39.651
Just being a panelist on a show
probably doesn't pay that much.

00:38:40.781 --> 00:38:43.081
At this rate, I'm worried
they'll never leave Onjeong.

00:38:43.481 --> 00:38:45.591
The psychic told me
to stay away from the Gongs.

00:38:46.751 --> 00:38:47.761
Darn it.

00:38:57.331 --> 00:39:01.641
Gosh, you're early.
I always arrive right on time.

00:39:02.001 --> 00:39:06.371
Being too early makes someone
who is on time feel awkward.

00:39:07.641 --> 00:39:10.041
What is it this time?

00:39:11.011 --> 00:39:12.111
So uptight.

00:39:13.751 --> 00:39:14.851
Here.

00:39:15.081 --> 00:39:18.891
This is something special,
just for you, Doctor.

00:39:21.561 --> 00:39:23.791
Mabluro Consulting?

00:39:24.121 --> 00:39:28.301
They handle real estate for clinics,
so they'll find the perfect buyer.

00:39:28.861 --> 00:39:32.031
You seem awfully worried
we'll end up staying in Onjeong.

00:39:33.171 --> 00:39:34.941
My, Doctor.

00:39:35.301 --> 00:39:39.111
You're less of a doctor
and more of a mind reader.

00:39:40.871 --> 00:39:42.011
You're right.

00:39:42.341 --> 00:39:45.181
I heard money's a bit tight,
so moving might be difficult.

00:39:45.881 --> 00:39:48.021
I genuinely want to help you.

00:39:48.621 --> 00:39:52.891
I'd really love for you to move.

00:39:53.891 --> 00:39:58.631
We'll be moving, so don't worry.
If you're finished, please leave.

00:39:59.291 --> 00:40:02.201
I'm meeting someone here any minute.

00:40:03.531 --> 00:40:04.871
Oh, and here he is now.

00:40:08.501 --> 00:40:10.501
My goodness, son!

00:40:11.941 --> 00:40:12.941
You're meeting...

00:40:13.611 --> 00:40:14.711
my son?

00:40:19.611 --> 00:40:21.311
I didn't realize
you two were together.

00:40:21.681 --> 00:40:23.881
So when you said you had an errand,
you meant meeting with Dr. Han?

00:40:24.321 --> 00:40:25.321
Why? What for?

00:40:25.751 --> 00:40:27.151
I'll explain at home.

00:40:28.821 --> 00:40:29.961
Okay, fine. Then...

00:40:30.621 --> 00:40:32.991
I'll be on my way.

00:40:34.231 --> 00:40:35.231
See you later.

00:40:46.041 --> 00:40:47.741
(Managing Director Yang Hyun Bin,
Taehan Group)

00:40:49.811 --> 00:40:50.811
A model?

00:40:51.341 --> 00:40:53.211
Ju Ah didn't mention anything to me.

00:40:53.651 --> 00:40:56.681
Ju Ah is a designer,
so marketing isn't her department.

00:40:58.551 --> 00:41:01.251
Is this for the same reason
as your stepmother's visit?

00:41:01.521 --> 00:41:03.761
You want to "help" us because
we're struggling financially?

00:41:05.431 --> 00:41:08.701
This was an official decision
made by the board of directors.

00:41:10.701 --> 00:41:11.701
I'm sorry.

00:41:11.971 --> 00:41:13.601
I've been under a lot of stress
lately.

00:41:14.031 --> 00:41:15.771
And I guess
it's made me a bit paranoid.

00:41:16.671 --> 00:41:17.671
Not at all.

00:41:18.071 --> 00:41:21.911
I apologize on behalf of my family
for their recent behavior.

00:41:28.081 --> 00:41:32.291
Since things are awkward between us,
may I ask why you're offering this?

00:41:32.651 --> 00:41:34.991
I'm sure there are
plenty of other candidates.

00:41:36.691 --> 00:41:41.391
Before making this offer,
I watched all your TV appearances.

00:41:42.001 --> 00:41:45.771
There was something you said
on a recent show.

00:41:47.001 --> 00:41:48.671
When you were introducing
Gong Ju Ah,

00:41:48.941 --> 00:41:51.141
you described her
as a "Fashion Therapist."

00:41:51.711 --> 00:41:55.011
- My daughter is a designer.
- What?

00:41:55.281 --> 00:41:59.251
She says that in their own way,
designers are healers, too.

00:42:00.051 --> 00:42:04.551
They help people's emotional health
by creating clothes that suit them.

00:42:04.851 --> 00:42:07.491
A "Fashion Therapist," if you will.

00:42:09.421 --> 00:42:11.631
I did say that. I remember now.

00:42:11.861 --> 00:42:13.491
Ju Ah often says it herself.

00:42:14.231 --> 00:42:17.101
That she's not just making clothes.
She's creating happiness.

00:42:18.871 --> 00:42:20.601
A doctor who heals minds...

00:42:20.931 --> 00:42:22.971
and a designer
who creates happiness.

00:42:23.601 --> 00:42:25.771
Isn't that
what a Fashion Therapist is?

00:42:27.211 --> 00:42:29.541
If you were to join us, Doctor...

00:42:30.241 --> 00:42:33.211
We could look after the hearts
of those who wear Taehan clothes...

00:42:33.981 --> 00:42:36.721
and honor the designer's conviction
to create happiness.

00:42:36.921 --> 00:42:38.821
I believe we can convey
all of that together.

00:42:42.861 --> 00:42:46.431
I haven't really paid much attention
to what Ju Ah does.

00:42:46.931 --> 00:42:49.961
I thought she'd follow our lead
and become a doctor someday.

00:42:50.201 --> 00:42:52.231
And that this was just a phase.

00:42:52.901 --> 00:42:53.971
Ju Ah...

00:42:54.271 --> 00:42:57.671
is so talented, we're lucky
the medical world didn't steal her.

00:42:58.141 --> 00:42:59.971
She's one of
Taehan's most valuable assets.

00:43:04.341 --> 00:43:05.411
Well, working with Ju Ah...

00:43:06.511 --> 00:43:08.521
I suppose that could...

00:43:09.381 --> 00:43:10.621
actually be nice.

00:43:12.351 --> 00:43:14.991
In that case,
please take a look at this.

00:43:16.461 --> 00:43:17.461
(Modeling Contract)

00:43:19.031 --> 00:43:21.291
We'll coordinate all the scheduling
around your availability...

00:43:21.631 --> 00:43:24.061
to make sure it doesn't interfere
with your work.

00:43:25.271 --> 00:43:29.841
Part of the proceeds will be donated
to a mental health support program.

00:43:31.001 --> 00:43:35.841
- Really?
- Yes. You'll get the fee upfront.

00:43:36.311 --> 00:43:40.181
I can assure you the compensation
is the best in the industry.

00:43:44.851 --> 00:43:47.051
Han Seong Mi is modeling for Taehan?

00:43:47.591 --> 00:43:48.591
Yes.

00:43:48.961 --> 00:43:51.761
My dear sister-in-law
must be so jealous.

00:43:52.631 --> 00:43:54.631
Are you upset?

00:43:54.901 --> 00:43:58.061
No, it's company business.
I need to keep my emotions aside.

00:43:58.401 --> 00:44:02.101
It may be business, but Hyun Bin
is still doing that family a favor.

00:44:02.641 --> 00:44:06.271
Tell me about it. It's amazing
how my son and I are so in sync.

00:44:06.541 --> 00:44:10.341
I worried for that family.
I'm glad they can afford the move.

00:44:11.141 --> 00:44:12.651
But hey, Hyun Bin.

00:44:13.481 --> 00:44:14.481
If I ever become famous,

00:44:15.121 --> 00:44:16.281
can you get me a modeling gig?

00:44:16.551 --> 00:44:18.351
Get famous first, then we'll talk.

00:44:19.321 --> 00:44:23.761
Man, if I could just get on TV once,
I could die happy. Right?

00:44:24.161 --> 00:44:25.631
On one of those
traditional medicine talk shows.

00:44:25.961 --> 00:44:27.031
If I went on a show like that,

00:44:27.591 --> 00:44:29.361
I'd take all of Korea by storm.

00:44:29.431 --> 00:44:33.371
Of course. The whole nation
would fall in love with you.

00:44:34.401 --> 00:44:37.801
Gosh,
why am I not getting any offers?

00:44:38.471 --> 00:44:39.771
I want to be on TV.

00:44:41.171 --> 00:44:42.181
I'd even settle for radio.

00:44:42.911 --> 00:44:43.981
Hello, everyone.

00:44:47.381 --> 00:44:48.381
What?

00:44:52.651 --> 00:44:53.651
Yes, hello.

00:44:55.661 --> 00:44:56.661
What was that?

00:44:57.521 --> 00:44:59.261
You're saying the pharmacy space
has been leased?

00:44:59.961 --> 00:45:01.491
But how?
They didn't even look at it.

00:45:04.001 --> 00:45:06.401
Is another pharmacy moving in
by any chance?

00:45:06.901 --> 00:45:07.901
No.

00:45:08.841 --> 00:45:13.171
I see. I was really hoping
it would stay a pharmacy.

00:45:13.871 --> 00:45:15.111
Actually, ma'am...

00:45:15.441 --> 00:45:20.051
The new tenant wants a pharmacy
to remain in that location.

00:45:20.311 --> 00:45:24.221
They'd like you to keep running it
until a new pharmacy can move in,

00:45:24.521 --> 00:45:27.591
and even offered to pay the rent
in the meantime.

00:45:27.991 --> 00:45:28.991
My goodness.

00:45:29.261 --> 00:45:33.031
No, I mean...
Who's this person to be so generous?

00:45:33.331 --> 00:45:37.501
They're a long-time local resident.
For the market seniors' convenience,

00:45:37.701 --> 00:45:39.601
they said they insist on doing it.

00:45:40.071 --> 00:45:43.201
And they offered to pay a premium
for the location.

00:45:44.441 --> 00:45:46.111
My gosh, are you serious?

00:45:46.971 --> 00:45:48.541
I don't know who it is, but...

00:45:48.781 --> 00:45:50.611
I'm so incredibly grateful.

00:45:51.811 --> 00:45:54.311
Okay, then. Take care.

00:45:59.251 --> 00:46:00.651
The talk went well.

00:46:02.491 --> 00:46:04.961
Make sure you keep it a secret
that I'm the one leasing it.

00:46:05.661 --> 00:46:06.661
Yes, sir.

00:46:06.931 --> 00:46:10.101
You can just wire the deposit
to this account.

00:46:10.731 --> 00:46:13.201
If I find a buyer for the pharmacy,
I'll connect them to you right away,

00:46:13.271 --> 00:46:15.471
and until then, you'll pay the rent.
Correct?

00:46:15.801 --> 00:46:16.941
Don't ask me again.

00:46:19.641 --> 00:46:21.271
Take care, sir.

00:46:26.951 --> 00:46:29.151
What? The clothes that you made?

00:46:29.481 --> 00:46:30.951
Our Seong Mi is going to wear them?

00:46:31.481 --> 00:46:34.551
It's not just me.
We're all working on it together.

00:46:34.821 --> 00:46:37.061
- Right, but still...
- You really had no idea?

00:46:37.191 --> 00:46:40.761
No, I figured
the Director wouldn't suggest it...

00:46:40.831 --> 00:46:42.301
since it could be awkward
with our family history.

00:46:42.931 --> 00:46:45.501
We're so grateful,
especially in a crisis like this.

00:46:46.171 --> 00:46:49.201
What are you talking about?
Our Seong Mi is the one helping out.

00:46:49.341 --> 00:46:51.541
Taehan should be thanking her.

00:46:51.701 --> 00:46:55.411
- He's right.
- Honey, this is just wonderful.

00:46:55.681 --> 00:46:59.211
Our Seong Mi, in a fashion show,
wearing an outfit by our Ju Ah.

00:46:59.651 --> 00:47:03.981
I'm so happy just thinking about it.
Your grandma can come watch, right?

00:47:04.281 --> 00:47:07.391
Of course.
I'll get you a front-row seat.

00:47:08.021 --> 00:47:09.291
I think I'm going to tear up.

00:47:11.121 --> 00:47:13.461
Honey, I guess
you can't tell Ju Ah...

00:47:13.931 --> 00:47:16.131
to give up on being a designer now,
can you?

00:47:17.061 --> 00:47:18.061
I guess not.

00:47:19.131 --> 00:47:23.171
I guess all I can do is pin my hopes
on Woo Jae now.

00:47:26.711 --> 00:47:29.141
How about I grab some beers
so we can make a toast?

00:47:29.441 --> 00:47:31.781
The pharmacy's taken care of,
and Mom's job is settled.

00:47:32.281 --> 00:47:34.251
Wait, but that's not all.

00:47:34.751 --> 00:47:37.521
I've also found a new doctor
for our clinic.

00:47:37.751 --> 00:47:39.291
- My goodness.
- Really? When?

00:47:39.351 --> 00:47:43.621
- Really? Are you serious?
- Yes. Retired from Icheon Hospital.

00:47:43.721 --> 00:47:44.721
Dr. Jo Tae Gwan.

00:47:45.961 --> 00:47:49.331
He reached out and said he wanted
to work in an underserved area.

00:47:49.401 --> 00:47:51.661
My, son, that's wonderful news.

00:47:52.271 --> 00:47:54.331
He said he's coming
to the clinic next week.

00:47:55.471 --> 00:47:56.901
- Uncle.
- Yes?

00:47:57.141 --> 00:47:58.571
So you changed your mind
about moving?

00:47:58.841 --> 00:48:00.671
What can you do?
You've got to go with the flow.

00:48:01.111 --> 00:48:02.441
But let's say
I'm walking down the street...

00:48:02.711 --> 00:48:05.611
and run into Dong Suk again.
The second I see her face,

00:48:05.881 --> 00:48:07.051
I might literally poop my pants.

00:48:08.881 --> 00:48:09.981
I could totally see that happening.

00:48:10.051 --> 00:48:13.421
Mom, won't it be awkward
working with the Director?

00:48:14.091 --> 00:48:15.761
I must say,
Bucket's son is a nice guy.

00:48:16.321 --> 00:48:19.631
- He has such a way with words.
- Is he as good as I am?

00:48:19.961 --> 00:48:22.601
That's right. He's just as charming
as my Woo Jae.

00:48:23.001 --> 00:48:25.201
What? Will you listen to her?

00:48:25.831 --> 00:48:27.871
Maybe it's because
he wasn't raised by Bucket.

00:48:28.231 --> 00:48:29.641
He turned out well.

00:48:34.011 --> 00:48:37.381
What's this? I thought you wanted
to find someone besides Dr. Han.

00:48:37.911 --> 00:48:39.551
You're telling me
you signed her over the weekend?

00:48:40.581 --> 00:48:43.251
She was getting many offers
from other brands.

00:48:43.381 --> 00:48:46.021
I feared we'd lose her if we waited,
so I moved fast to lock her in.

00:48:46.751 --> 00:48:48.091
But doesn't that put us over budget?

00:48:48.761 --> 00:48:50.091
On top of that, an advance payment?

00:48:51.421 --> 00:48:55.031
That's what it took to get her.
Don't worry. Just trust me.

00:48:55.531 --> 00:48:58.731
She'll boost our brand's value
far beyond our investment.

00:49:03.501 --> 00:49:07.571
Your mother will open the show
wearing the outfit you designed.

00:49:07.941 --> 00:49:11.241
Then you two will bow at the finale.
I thought it'd be a great moment.

00:49:12.011 --> 00:49:13.011
Goodness.

00:49:13.311 --> 00:49:15.451
He said my being nice
was making it hard for him.

00:49:15.451 --> 00:49:17.121
So why is he being nice?

00:49:18.181 --> 00:49:19.751
He's making it impossible
to move on.

00:49:30.401 --> 00:49:31.431
(Taehan Group)

00:49:32.501 --> 00:49:33.501
My gosh.

00:49:34.371 --> 00:49:36.841
Hey, hold on.

00:49:38.301 --> 00:49:42.141
- What is it?
- Why did you pay it all at once?

00:49:42.911 --> 00:49:44.811
Are you trying
to get on my mom's good side?

00:49:45.781 --> 00:49:46.811
What are you talking about?

00:49:47.311 --> 00:49:49.651
It wasn't a personal favor.

00:49:49.851 --> 00:49:51.851
This is coming from the guy
who gave me a hard time...

00:49:51.851 --> 00:49:53.451
for buying him cold medicine?

00:49:54.721 --> 00:49:58.521
- Excuse me, Ms. Gong Ju Ah.
- What? Pulling the Director card?

00:49:58.761 --> 00:49:59.761
Unbelievable.

00:50:01.661 --> 00:50:04.701
Yang Hyun Bin.
This isn't the office.

00:50:06.671 --> 00:50:11.441
Thanks to you, my dream came true,
and my family gets to move.

00:50:13.471 --> 00:50:14.471
Thank you.

00:50:16.241 --> 00:50:17.241
Director.

00:50:29.761 --> 00:50:30.761
My gosh.

00:50:31.491 --> 00:50:33.031
Is it true that
Dr. Gong's family is moving?

00:50:33.431 --> 00:50:36.301
Yes, they're moving everything,
even the clinic,

00:50:36.601 --> 00:50:40.171
which means the association's
presidency will go to Dr. Yang.

00:50:40.501 --> 00:50:42.771
Councilor Hwang
will be disappointed.

00:50:42.771 --> 00:50:44.301
He tried hard to win over Dr. Gong.

00:50:45.101 --> 00:50:47.741
Well, for me, it's a huge relief.

00:50:48.111 --> 00:50:50.381
With him out of the picture,
we're next in line, right?

00:50:52.151 --> 00:50:54.681
You really have no pride, do you?

00:50:55.251 --> 00:50:57.251
That's right, I don't.

00:50:57.251 --> 00:50:59.491
Pride won't make me
a councilor's wife.

00:51:01.821 --> 00:51:02.821
Oh, right.

00:51:03.161 --> 00:51:05.531
- I have some good news for you.
- What?

00:51:06.291 --> 00:51:08.491
- What is it?
- Councilor Hwang's daughter...

00:51:08.701 --> 00:51:10.801
wants your son's number.

00:51:10.801 --> 00:51:12.701
- My gosh, really?
- Yes.

00:51:12.701 --> 00:51:15.231
Why? I heard his wife
was absolutely furious.

00:51:15.401 --> 00:51:18.001
She's headstrong and
does whatever she wants.

00:51:18.401 --> 00:51:21.311
She seemed interested when she heard
he's a director at Taehan Group.

00:51:21.411 --> 00:51:24.241
My goodness, what do I do?

00:51:25.281 --> 00:51:30.221
It's good luck to avoid the Gongs.
Gosh, I'm so happy!

00:51:36.361 --> 00:51:37.361
Director.

00:51:38.021 --> 00:51:42.201
I'll practice my presentation.
Could you give me some feedback?

00:51:42.531 --> 00:51:45.631
Sure, just let me know when,
and I'll make time.

00:51:46.101 --> 00:51:47.101
Okay.

00:51:48.331 --> 00:51:49.341
What?

00:51:51.201 --> 00:51:52.411
Oh, one moment...

00:51:52.411 --> 00:51:56.811
- Go ahead, take it. I don't mind.
- Oh, okay.

00:52:00.681 --> 00:52:02.481
Yes, stepmother, what is it?

00:52:03.881 --> 00:52:04.921
A blind date?

00:52:11.561 --> 00:52:14.891
(Fantom)

00:52:18.501 --> 00:52:20.801
He wouldn't go on a blind date,
would he?

00:52:23.741 --> 00:52:26.971
(Taehan Group)

00:52:27.071 --> 00:52:28.841
I don't do blind dates.

00:52:29.141 --> 00:52:31.481
I'm going back to Argentina
in one year.

00:52:32.011 --> 00:52:34.811
Just meet her once.
Please do that for me, okay?

00:52:35.481 --> 00:52:39.021
She's tied to your dad's business.
I'm asking you, Hyun Bin. Please.

00:52:39.691 --> 00:52:40.691
Oh, boy...

00:52:42.461 --> 00:52:45.461
Man, I should've left before eating.
I still feel weird about it.

00:52:45.931 --> 00:52:49.531
Why make us order the same dish?
Even the Koreas aren't unified yet.

00:52:50.001 --> 00:52:51.361
But I saw a glimmer of hope.

00:52:51.861 --> 00:52:53.171
What? Hope for reunification?

00:52:54.501 --> 00:52:56.171
Between you and the Director,
I mean.

00:52:56.701 --> 00:52:59.311
Hey, didn't you say
your mom likes the Director?

00:53:00.211 --> 00:53:02.511
It means she's comfortable enough
to work with him, that's all.

00:53:04.311 --> 00:53:06.951
You know, he's kind of cute.

00:53:07.381 --> 00:53:11.751
He says it's professional,
but he swooped in to save you.

00:53:11.951 --> 00:53:14.991
Man, that's some pure devotion.
Right? A truly devoted man.

00:53:35.981 --> 00:53:37.511
It's not exactly pure devotion,

00:53:37.981 --> 00:53:40.051
and I don't think
he's the devoted type.

00:53:42.751 --> 00:53:44.881
What? What's with that two-shot?

00:53:45.421 --> 00:53:46.421
A blind date.

00:53:47.391 --> 00:53:48.391
For real?

00:53:50.621 --> 00:53:51.761
Why do I find this so ridiculous?

00:53:52.961 --> 00:53:57.401
Hey, if I'm this baffled,
I can only imagine how you feel.

00:53:59.831 --> 00:54:01.401
Wow, I'm really disappointed
in the Director.

00:54:06.311 --> 00:54:07.371
Hey.

00:54:11.941 --> 00:54:14.551
You seem surprised
that I showed up unannounced.

00:54:15.351 --> 00:54:17.481
I guess this is how
blind dates work these days.

00:54:18.221 --> 00:54:20.991
I'm a little thrown off
by you coming to my office.

00:54:23.421 --> 00:54:24.621
I was in the neighborhood.

00:54:25.361 --> 00:54:27.931
And I was also curious...

00:54:28.091 --> 00:54:31.301
to see how you'd react
if I just showed up.

00:54:32.301 --> 00:54:34.031
I'm not sure what you've heard,

00:54:34.471 --> 00:54:37.701
but I'm planning to return
to Argentina in one year.

00:54:39.411 --> 00:54:40.411
That's great.

00:54:41.141 --> 00:54:42.541
Then why don't we date
for just one year?

00:54:43.911 --> 00:54:46.851
No. There's someone I like.

00:54:47.411 --> 00:54:48.411
Your mother...

00:54:49.081 --> 00:54:50.321
didn't seem to know
anything about that.

00:54:50.681 --> 00:54:54.351
Since I'm only here for one year,
I'm just admiring her from afar.

00:54:55.961 --> 00:54:57.261
So devoted.

00:54:59.161 --> 00:55:00.361
You're just my type.

00:55:17.581 --> 00:55:20.481
If he wasn't sure of his feelings,
why would he help me?

00:55:20.851 --> 00:55:23.251
He said it was hard to move on,
so how can he do that so soon?

00:55:23.321 --> 00:55:25.721
Seriously.
This is ridiculous, I swear.

00:55:27.691 --> 00:55:28.691
I mean...

00:55:29.321 --> 00:55:30.521
Why am I so upset?

00:55:31.661 --> 00:55:34.291
It's not like
we're anything to each other.

00:55:40.671 --> 00:55:42.501
The house gets plenty of sun,

00:55:42.501 --> 00:55:44.171
the yard is spacious...
It's perfect.

00:55:44.241 --> 00:55:48.141
- I know, Chief. They're rare.
- Tell me about it.

00:55:48.211 --> 00:55:50.741
- This is a great place to work out.
- Hey, look at the vegetable garden.

00:55:51.541 --> 00:55:54.951
We can plant peppers and lettuce.
That'd be nice, right?

00:55:55.181 --> 00:55:57.281
- You should plant tomatoes, too.
- Of course.

00:55:58.181 --> 00:56:00.151
I'm so glad you like it.

00:56:00.491 --> 00:56:04.021
My wife has always dreamed
of having her own vegetable garden.

00:56:04.461 --> 00:56:07.931
Yes. Since it gets so much sun,

00:56:08.291 --> 00:56:11.461
anything you plant in the spring
should grow really well.

00:56:12.331 --> 00:56:16.271
We had to keep it quiet,
so I asked through my contacts,

00:56:16.341 --> 00:56:18.841
and what do you know?
The Chief was moving to Onjeong.

00:56:18.971 --> 00:56:21.371
Right. I was surprised to find out
that you were the one...

00:56:21.441 --> 00:56:22.981
coming to see the house, Chief.

00:56:23.041 --> 00:56:26.951
Yes. My mother-in-law lives
pretty far from here.

00:56:27.051 --> 00:56:31.581
Her health has worsened recently.
It's too far for us to visit often,

00:56:32.221 --> 00:56:34.321
so we decided it was time
for her to come and live with us.

00:56:36.391 --> 00:56:38.921
Your mother-in-law must be thrilled.

00:56:39.361 --> 00:56:40.491
I hope so.

00:56:41.531 --> 00:56:45.531
- Would you like to look inside?
- Yes.

00:56:48.671 --> 00:56:51.041
Chief, are you serious?
I can really have the room upstairs?

00:56:51.101 --> 00:56:53.941
Of course. Hey, it's way better
than that tiny room you had, right?

00:56:54.071 --> 00:56:57.041
Are you kidding me? It's way better.
And it's near the substation, too.

00:56:57.041 --> 00:57:01.751
- Yes.
- But you must be sad.

00:57:03.881 --> 00:57:07.121
Even after you move,
I hope you'll think of this as home.

00:57:07.221 --> 00:57:08.891
Feel free to stop by anytime.

00:57:10.121 --> 00:57:12.631
I poured so much love
into this house,

00:57:12.961 --> 00:57:14.361
so I was worried
I'd be heartbroken to leave.

00:57:14.691 --> 00:57:17.131
But knowing a kind person like you
is moving in...

00:57:17.501 --> 00:57:18.861
really puts my heart at ease.

00:57:21.501 --> 00:57:23.741
- My goodness.
- The upstairs is really nice.

00:57:36.821 --> 00:57:37.921
What are you doing here all alone?

00:57:38.751 --> 00:57:40.121
What are you doing here?

00:57:41.021 --> 00:57:42.621
I was heading home from work
and saw the light was on.

00:57:42.891 --> 00:57:44.091
Oh, well...

00:57:44.361 --> 00:57:47.531
I was just getting things ready
for the new doctor to take over.

00:57:49.361 --> 00:57:51.461
Tomorrow's the clinic's
40th anniversary, isn't it?

00:57:52.031 --> 00:57:53.031
Yes.

00:57:53.671 --> 00:57:55.301
Tomorrow,
I'll have to tell the patients...

00:57:55.531 --> 00:57:57.171
that we're leaving.

00:57:58.471 --> 00:57:59.541
Are you taking this hard?

00:58:03.711 --> 00:58:04.711
Seong Mi.

00:58:05.711 --> 00:58:07.051
What's gotten into you?

00:58:08.281 --> 00:58:10.651
You've been through so much
on your own all this time.

00:58:11.381 --> 00:58:14.621
From now on, so my successful
Seong Mi can go even further,

00:58:14.821 --> 00:58:16.891
I'll take good care of our family...

00:58:17.321 --> 00:58:18.721
and be the most supportive husband
I can be.

00:58:19.361 --> 00:58:21.761
My success is all because of you.

00:58:23.061 --> 00:58:24.401
Isn't it thanks to my mom?

00:58:24.701 --> 00:58:27.331
If I hadn't met you,
how would I have met your mother?

00:58:28.531 --> 00:58:29.701
You've got a point.

00:58:31.601 --> 00:58:33.571
Come here. Let me give you a hug.

00:58:33.971 --> 00:58:37.711
My, what an unexpected treat!
My goodness.

00:58:51.591 --> 00:58:54.731
It's a relief that the police chief
is the one moving in.

00:58:56.061 --> 00:58:57.061
Is it...

00:58:57.531 --> 00:58:59.801
really okay for me
to do this on my own?

00:59:00.601 --> 00:59:03.341
You're asking that now,
after you've already sold the house?

00:59:05.471 --> 00:59:08.771
I'm just worried because I did this
without telling your father.

00:59:09.781 --> 00:59:13.811
What's there to discuss?
Grandfather left this house to you.

00:59:14.211 --> 00:59:17.181
Besides, Dad does whatever he wants.
Why shouldn't you?

00:59:17.881 --> 00:59:18.881
I guess you're right.

00:59:19.191 --> 00:59:20.421
Just do whatever you want.
All of it.

00:59:30.831 --> 00:59:33.671
That spring, when forsythias bloomed
all along the wall,

00:59:34.371 --> 00:59:36.271
was when I first came to this house.

00:59:37.501 --> 00:59:40.811
So much laughter, tears, joy,
and sorrow...

00:59:41.211 --> 00:59:43.341
have all been shared
under this roof.

00:59:46.111 --> 00:59:47.311
And today,

00:59:47.851 --> 00:59:50.821
this house, which held the memory
of the years you were gone...

00:59:51.481 --> 00:59:53.251
I have decided to leave it behind.

00:59:54.421 --> 00:59:57.161
Please, I hope you're not
disappointed in me.

01:00:06.101 --> 01:00:10.071
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

01:00:10.141 --> 01:00:11.641
(Onjeong News)

01:00:13.811 --> 01:00:16.241
(Onjeong News)

01:00:16.311 --> 01:00:17.781
(A Friendship
Spanning Half a Century)

01:00:17.841 --> 01:00:19.251
(Power Duo Leading Onjeong Market)

01:00:19.311 --> 01:00:20.811
"A Friendship
Spanning Half a Century,"

01:00:20.811 --> 01:00:22.921
"Power Duo Leading Onjeong Market."

01:00:23.621 --> 01:00:25.481
They look like total besties
in the photo.

01:00:26.521 --> 01:00:27.751
It doesn't do me justice.

01:00:28.051 --> 01:00:31.061
They should've used a better photo.
How old is this photo anyway?

01:00:31.321 --> 01:00:34.431
"Leading the 16th Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association..."

01:00:34.491 --> 01:00:36.661
"are President Gong Jeong Han
and Vice President Yang Dong Ik..."

01:00:36.731 --> 01:00:38.761
Actually,
he's the President now, Dong Suk.

01:00:40.201 --> 01:00:42.901
"Childhood friends
for over 50 years,"

01:00:42.901 --> 01:00:45.041
"they have faced everything
together."

01:00:46.511 --> 01:00:47.741
Those were the days.

01:00:49.381 --> 01:00:52.711
"Their long-standing friendship
and memories..."

01:00:53.051 --> 01:00:55.811
"transcend the history
of Onjeong Market."

01:00:56.251 --> 01:00:58.451
"Moving forward,
they will remain..."

01:00:58.881 --> 01:01:01.051
"each other's
most steadfast companions."

01:01:06.431 --> 01:01:08.061
It really doesn't do me justice.

01:01:08.661 --> 01:01:10.231
But hey, it's a good picture.

01:01:11.231 --> 01:01:12.971
That punk Jeong Han looks better,
though.

01:01:14.701 --> 01:01:16.501
Maybe
I should just cut him out of it.

01:01:16.571 --> 01:01:19.511
(Doctor of Korean Medicine,
Yang Dong Ik)

01:01:23.311 --> 01:01:25.381
Yes, this is Dr. Yang Dong Ik.

01:01:27.951 --> 01:01:28.951
A TV station?

01:01:30.321 --> 01:01:31.421
From the show "Human Theater"?

01:01:33.391 --> 01:01:35.551
I'm a huge fan of that show!

01:01:37.191 --> 01:01:38.291
What's this about?

01:01:39.761 --> 01:01:41.991
Oh, you saw the local paper?

01:01:42.731 --> 01:01:43.931
You did. I see.

01:01:45.331 --> 01:01:47.471
You want me on the show? Me?

01:01:48.671 --> 01:01:49.671
Me?

01:01:51.701 --> 01:01:55.341
Yes! Of course, I'll do it.
Hold on a second.

01:01:55.871 --> 01:01:58.441
Am I dreaming?
Is this really happening?

01:01:58.911 --> 01:02:01.481
Yes! Of course, I'll do it.

01:02:01.981 --> 01:02:03.321
What? There's a condition?

01:02:03.581 --> 01:02:06.591
What is it? Tell me anything.
I'm all ears.

01:02:07.751 --> 01:02:09.721
- He's coming.
- My gosh.

01:02:09.891 --> 01:02:10.961
Gosh, you scared me.

01:02:11.361 --> 01:02:13.491
- Oh, you shouldn't have.
- Congratulations.

01:02:13.561 --> 01:02:14.961
- Congratulations.
- Goodness.

01:02:15.831 --> 01:02:16.831
Thank you.

01:02:18.101 --> 01:02:20.971
Gosh, what's all this?

01:02:21.031 --> 01:02:23.941
- I'm speechless.
- How did you have time for this?

01:02:24.071 --> 01:02:27.771
All right. Congratulations
on your 40th anniversary!

01:02:27.841 --> 01:02:30.381
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

01:02:32.851 --> 01:02:35.381
(Thank you!)

01:02:35.451 --> 01:02:38.121
(Dr. Gong Jeong Han)

01:02:44.861 --> 01:02:48.131
Okay, let's talk again soon.
Thank you. Bye.

01:02:48.191 --> 01:02:49.561
Yes, we'll be in touch.

01:02:54.371 --> 01:02:58.201
Yes! Nice!

01:03:02.541 --> 01:03:03.541
Gong Jeong Han...

01:03:04.211 --> 01:03:05.941
That punk...

01:03:07.611 --> 01:03:08.651
Blow them out.

01:03:10.351 --> 01:03:13.251
(Happy 40th Anniversary!)

01:03:16.461 --> 01:03:20.231
I'm so overwhelmed.
My palms are sweating.

01:03:21.491 --> 01:03:22.531
Okay.

01:03:23.301 --> 01:03:27.571
Well, I have some difficult news
to share today.

01:03:28.071 --> 01:03:29.301
What am I going to do?

01:03:29.941 --> 01:03:31.171
Hey, what's with you?

01:03:31.971 --> 01:03:33.241
- Are you crying?
- I think the Doctor's crying.

01:03:34.511 --> 01:03:37.411
Oh, my brother is
just moved to tears.

01:03:37.811 --> 01:03:41.051
Yes, he's just really touched.
Let's give him a round of applause!

01:03:41.911 --> 01:03:43.051
Don't cry.

01:03:44.281 --> 01:03:45.281
Right.

01:03:45.821 --> 01:03:49.051
Thank you all so much.

01:03:50.561 --> 01:03:53.691
Sometimes like family,
other times like friends,

01:03:54.661 --> 01:03:58.701
you've always shown me
such warm love and encouragement.

01:03:59.331 --> 01:04:03.041
I believe that's how this clinic
and I have both made it this far.

01:04:05.971 --> 01:04:08.041
But on a day like today,

01:04:08.841 --> 01:04:12.851
it really pains me
to be the one to bring this up.

01:04:15.251 --> 01:04:16.251
What's going on?

01:04:20.021 --> 01:04:22.651
The clinic
I have poured my heart into...

01:04:23.191 --> 01:04:25.261
The Gong Myeong
Jeong Dae Han Clinic.

01:04:29.291 --> 01:04:30.301
I will now have to...

01:04:31.761 --> 01:04:34.331
- let it become a part of...
- Hold on!

01:04:34.401 --> 01:04:35.731
(Happy 40th Anniversary!)

01:04:39.771 --> 01:04:41.241
(Happy 40th Anniversary!)

01:05:12.034 --> 01:05:14.034
Dramaday.me